<section class="section" style="background-color: var(--color-white);">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Legacy & Influence</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-sm" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Responsive Design Era</h3>
        <p>
          Flat design's simple shapes and colors scale perfectly across devices. No texture 
          files to load. Clean SVG icons work at any size. Perfect timing for mobile-first era.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-sm" style="color: var(--color-success);">Performance Benefits</h3>
        <p>
          Flat interfaces load faster without heavy texture images. Simpler rendering improves 
          performance on all devices. Essential for mobile web and emerging markets.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-sm" style="color: var(--color-warning);">Design System Foundation</h3>
        <p>
          Flat design's component-based approach enabled modern design systems. Reusable 
          elements with clear states became standard. Influenced frameworks worldwide.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-sm" style="color: var(--color-danger);">Evolution to Flat 2.0</h3>
        <p>
          Pure flat design evolved to add subtle depth for usability. Shadows returned to 
          show hierarchy. Motion design added dimension. Balance between aesthetic and function.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
